[{'number': 22, 'created': '2024-01-18 12:56:47.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/storpool.py', 'releasenotes/notes/bug-1939241-storpool-attach-encrypted-volumes-783c723683b8f9a9.yaml', 'cinder/tests/unit/volume/drivers/test_storpool.py'], 'message': 'StorPool: drop _attach_volume() and _detach_volume()

commit_message:
StorPool: drop _attach_volume() and _detach_volume()

Our os-brick connector already handles the "keep track of which volume
is attached for what reason" calls to storpool.spopenstack. However,
we need to explicitly specify the access mode in initialize_connection()
now, since our os-brick connector does not know how to divine it yet.
(this will come later with the "attach snapshot" functionality)

Incidentally, this fixes the "create an encrypted volume" flow, since
our _attach_volume() implementation never actually returned a connector
in the attachment info...

Change-Id: I5da7ae04b87b4fd52a682a6545060e852174f6c8
Closes-Bug: #1939241

subject: Allow circular dependencies for openstack-helm projects
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2020-07-19 15:16:05.000000000', 'files': ['zuul/main.yaml'], 'message': 'Allow circular dependencies for openstack-helm projects

Openstack-helm projects reuse job definitions and related ansible code
from each other for testing purposes to avoid code duplication not
supporting strongly dependent changes introduced to multiple repositories.

This commit allows circular dependencies for openstack-helm projects to
avoid temporarily disabling jobs in one of projects for strongly dependent
changes.

Change-Id: Id11cfa0e961ec2e9c16506a21a7859b284ecdc0a
Signed-off-by: Andrii Ostapenko <andrii.ostapenko@att.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Allow circular dependencies for openstack-helm projects

Openstack-helm projects reuse job definitions and related ansible code
from each other for testing purposes to avoid code duplication not
supporting strongly dependent changes introduced to multiple repositories.

This commit allows circular dependencies for openstack-helm projects to
avoid temporarily disabling jobs in one of projects for strongly dependent
changes.

Change-Id: Id11cfa0e961ec2e9c16506a21a7859b284ecdc0a
Signed-off-by: Andrii Ostapenko <andrii.ostapenko@att.com>

commit_message:
Fix incorrect mock usage

test_configure_global_cluster() is using 'has_calls',
but that does not exist in the unittest.mock library.
Use 'assert_has_calls' as eventually this will cause
a test error.

Change-Id: Ica1fa7daaf6c90d988805c33352d3e4246af080d

commit_message:
Improve platform mocking

Patch out charmhelpers.osplatform.get_platform() and
charmhelpers.core.host.lsb_release() globally in the unit tests to
insulate the unit tests from the platform that the unit tests are being
run on.

Copied from
https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/charm-cinder-backup/+/899200

Change-Id: Ibb36344b1c30492b8a822fb48f753c6bdf6ca279

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2023-03-21 02:07:28.000000000', 'files': ['setup.cfg'], 'message': "setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: I3e48ef3755fdbbfe65c2a46b817e02f4a3cadae3
"}]
commit_message:
setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: I3e48ef3755fdbbfe65c2a46b817e02f4a3cadae3

subject: Add devstack-gate back to central config for retirement prep
revisions:

Several years ago all of devstack-gate's zuul config was moved into
devstack-gate proper. We need to keep the official jobs that do github
syncing here in project-config and we need to add noop-jobs to
project-config in order to "remove" the repo content in preparation for

Change-Id: Ib7aa64663cd6306e69b49e15e80419230079a8a8

commit_message:
Add devstack-gate back to central config for retirement prep

Several years ago all of devstack-gate's zuul config was moved into
devstack-gate proper. We need to keep the official jobs that do github
syncing here in project-config and we need to add noop-jobs to
project-config in order to "remove" the repo content in preparation for
its retirement. Do that here.

Followup changes will retire the repo then eventually make it back to
this repo to remove the config I have just added.

Change-Id: Ib7aa64663cd6306e69b49e15e80419230079a8a8

commit_message:
Resolve bug with long time for loading node group template page

In this patch I implement work with ajax for loading node group
template and simplify it process. If user click on tab for
configuration some process, sahara-dashboard send ajax-request
and load this tab.

Change-Id: Ied6733403ced3c2b2cddd92a81d5087e2c58e771
Closes-bug: 1430112

commit_message:
setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: Ie95246ca228a4f2c5054407535130e1aaf0fd140

subject: setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2023-06-12 07:45:07.000000000', 'files': ['setup.cfg'], 'message': "setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: I2791b0ffe7f787ff2d28bee04a10afbe04cd950d
"}]
commit_message:
setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: I2791b0ffe7f787ff2d28bee04a10afbe04cd950d

subject: Bump oslo.* and pbr version to support >=py38
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2022-06-24 02:10:39.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', '.zuul.yaml', 'lower-constraints.txt', 'setup.cfg'], 'message': 'Bump oslo.* and pbr version to support >=py38

In zed cycle, OpenStack projects and oslo lib
has dropped the py3.6 and py3.7 support

- https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/runtimes/zed.html

I also decrepated oslo-log < 5.0.0, so we should bump oslo.log>=5.0.0.

Because of oslo.log>=5.0.0 depends on oslo.i18n>=3.20.0 as below, so we
also need to upgrade oslo.i18n.

The conflict is caused by:
    The user requested oslo.utils>=3.33.0
    oslo-log 5.0.0 depends on oslo.utils>=3.36.0
    The user requested (constraint) oslo-utils==3.33.0

Change-Id: I9e52deda308339f7b0f1f8138dcf0345ccaa37cb
'}]
commit_message:
Bump oslo.* and pbr version to support >=py38

In zed cycle, OpenStack projects and oslo lib
has dropped the py3.6 and py3.7 support

- https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/runtimes/zed.html

I also decrepated oslo-log < 5.0.0, so we should bump oslo.log>=5.0.0.

Because of oslo.log>=5.0.0 depends on oslo.i18n>=3.20.0 as below, so we
also need to upgrade oslo.i18n.

The conflict is caused by:
    The user requested oslo.utils>=3.33.0
    oslo-log 5.0.0 depends on oslo.utils>=3.36.0
    The user requested (constraint) oslo-utils==3.33.0

Change-Id: I9e52deda308339f7b0f1f8138dcf0345ccaa37cb

commit_message:
Adapt to new jsonschema versions

This change provides fixes that were dectected by unit
test failures with new jsonschema (and py310).

The types argument has been removed in favor of providing a
type_checker to jsonschema.validators.extend:
https://github.com/python-jsonschema/jsonschema/issues/577

This change also refactors additional type checks after the
documentation here to get past many of the remaining failures:
https://python-jsonschema.readthedocs.io/en/latest/validate/#validating-with-additional-types

It also fixes the format used for a few hostname format tests
to idn-hostname and this adds idna as test requirements,
which seems to be included anyway through other dependencies.

Story: #2010192
Change-Id: Ifed2240a1b3460a174d24415ee53d64c1b06c3c5

commit_message:
Fix the buildimages jobs: ensure-tox role

- call ensure-tox and use its output.
  tox is not available by default on the images anymore.
- try to workaround the issue with newer pip and old
  system setuptools, see:
  * https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/issues/1694#issuecomment-466010982
- refact the base buildimages job a bit and call the bindep
  role from the pre phase, where it belongs more "naturally".

Change-Id: I2f8736c63b2e1c4360b7175cf12cf71a2ea4e4ff

commit_message:
Correct edp-spark workflow dir permission

edp spark engine places job binary and workflow
dir on the /tmp directory. The owner of these
files and dor are image user. Whereas spark job
is normally fired as spark user who doesn't
have access to these files. As a result spark
job fail with permission denied error as
shown in the logs provided in story.

This behaviour is visible when the image is
hardened which  changes the default file
permission that are stored in /tmp.

This fix proposes to explicitly provide
required access level on the files
under /tmp that are needed by spark job.

Change-Id: I23dffa7b0b8b44ba2deeb855839cb078d1e44852
Story: #2003414
Task: #24558

commit_message:
Force recover hdp cluster from error state

Often time ambari fails during installation or service
starting stage. This is quiet prominent when  there is
a large number of nodes in the cluster. While it is
possible to  recover this stage from ambari dashboard
by simply restarting the failed services or reinstalling the
failed components, sahara has no way to  know this status
and as a result the cluster remians useless to sahara with
status as error.

Assuming the manual step from ambari dashboard to restart
the cluster has been already performed , this patch provides
a facility to let shara activate the status and make it
usable. The first part of this patch is to provide a  cluster
update api call with force_status_toactive: true to change
perform necessary checks and change the status

The second part will be  to provide this facility from
client and the dashboard.

Change-Id: I6f5bc6127ab8cc130592ad240017a2232584dd8a
Story: #2003176
Task: #24510

subject: Fix dependencies for lower-constraints
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2022-03-03 14:15:33.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'lower-constraints.txt'], 'message': 'Fix dependencies for lower-constraints

Pip introduced new dependency resolver in some months ago, which
reveals multiple dependency conflicts:

* openstacksdk 0.36.0 already requires keystoneauth1>=3.16.0
  so set the boundary to make the lower-constraint job happy.
* Likewise, python-openstackclient 5.2.0 requires both
  python-novaclient 15.1.0 and python-keystoneclient 3.22.0.
* openstacksdk 0.36.0 requires os-service-types>=1.7.0
* flake8 3.7.9 requires at least mccabe 0.6.0

Change-Id: Ie524538e6ebc8cf8da857062ff4930e82955db1d
'}]
commit_message:
Fix dependencies for lower-constraints

Pip introduced new dependency resolver in some months ago, which
reveals multiple dependency conflicts:

* openstacksdk 0.36.0 already requires keystoneauth1>=3.16.0
  so set the boundary to make the lower-constraint job happy.
* Likewise, python-openstackclient 5.2.0 requires both
  python-novaclient 15.1.0 and python-keystoneclient 3.22.0.
* openstacksdk 0.36.0 requires os-service-types>=1.7.0
* flake8 3.7.9 requires at least mccabe 0.6.0

Change-Id: Ie524538e6ebc8cf8da857062ff4930e82955db1d

commit_message:
Update stable branches jobs on master gate

we have stable/2023.1 and stable/zed also present
and supported so we should add their job on master
gate to keep branchless tempest plugins compatible
to stable branch.

This also removes the old EM stable branches

commit_message:
Stop to use the __future__ module.

The __future__ module [1] was used in this context to ensure compatibility
between python 2 and python 3.

We previously dropped the support of python 2.7 [2] and now we only support
python 3 so we don't need to continue to use this module and the imports
listed below.

Imports commonly used and their related PEPs:
- `division` is related to PEP 238 [3]
- `print_function` is related to PEP 3105 [4]
- `unicode_literals` is related to PEP 3112 [5]
- `with_statement` is related to PEP 343 [6]
- `absolute_import` is related to PEP 328 [7]

[1] https://docs.python.org/3/library/__future__.html
[2] https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/selected/ussuri/drop-py27.html
[3] https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0238
[4] https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3105
[5] https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3112
[6] https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0343
[7] https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0328

Change-Id: I997db26a6f50d0ff5771c11946c01f942c39a24a

commit_message:
Add servicing states to states doc, fix state diagram

Good news, pydot (original) is maintained again and pydot2 apparently is
not. By switching to pydot instead of the fork, svg generation works
now.

regenerated diagram.

rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

commit_message:
Replace .testr.conf with .stestr.conf

In this change [1] os_testr changed under the covers from using
testr to stestr, so that we now get the following warning:

 ostestr.py:120:
 UserWarning: No .stestr.conf file found in the CWD.
 Please create one to to replace the .testr.conf. You can find a
 script to do this in the stestr git repository.

So remove the .testr.conf and add .stestr.conf which was
generated using a utility script as documented here [2].

[1] Id7cb2a39a8308f1413608dcf19273a1d7f33592e
[2] https://media.readthedocs.org/pdf/stestr/stable/stestr.pdf

Change-Id: Ib03d62bea8b2c28847943cd891776cf118e821d6

subject: setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2021-05-04 02:12:57.000000000', 'files': ['setup.cfg'], 'message': "setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: I5d5288aeef95c649755c2a62870c4e5c451d4b76
"}]
commit_message:
setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: I5d5288aeef95c649755c2a62870c4e5c451d4b76

commit_message:
Dropping lower constraints testing

We facing errors related to the new pip resolver, this
topic was discussed on the ML and QA team proposed to
to test lower-constraints [1].

I propose to drop this test because the complexity and recurring pain needed
to maintain that now exceeds the benefits provided by this mechanismes.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-discuss/2020-December/019390.html

Change-Id: I83e37396aee03802ec17a824b7550608863852b1

commit_message:
setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of
dash-separated options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported
in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores.
Without this, we see 'UserWarning' messages
like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

Change-Id: Ia123a2c96ffa956ada3f6692cbb3fe77a6cb97f2

commit_message:
Added app for MS Exchange Server 2013

PoC version, not ready for production.
App does ExchangeServer+ActiveDirectory *standalone* deployment.
This helps during dev-test stage since it saves time for deployment & doesn't require
additional resources (the only VM is used).
The plan is to make Exchange app as a separate and to create an option to choose the AD domain.

This app is tested on Windows Server 2012 R2 image with the following
prerequisites being additionally installed:
  - Microsoft Office 2010 Filter Packs - Version 2.0
  - Microsoft Office 2010 Filter Packs - Version 2.0 - Service Pack 1
  - Microsoft Unified Communications Managed API 4.0

Change-Id: I2b3164c766e23a7e845306406f254f9d1cda8da3

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated

commit_message:
setup.cfg: Replace dashes with underscores

Setuptools v54.1.0 introduces a warning that the use of dash-separated
options in 'setup.cfg' will not be supported in a future version [1].
Get ahead of the issue by replacing the dashes with underscores. Without
this, we see 'UserWarning' messages like the following on new enough
versions of setuptools:

  UserWarning: Usage of dash-separated 'description-file' will not be
  supported in future versions. Please use the underscore name
  'description_file' instead

[1] https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/a2e9ae4cb

Change-Id: Ie044a83fe33fe8b7e920eb7f7892bb00acb418a2

subject: [CI] Install dependencies for docs target
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2022-04-28 18:00:59.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': "[CI] Install dependencies for docs target

When tox 'docs' target is called, first it installs the dependencies
(listed in 'deps') in 'installdeps' phase, then it installs murano
(with its requirements) in 'develop-inst' phase. In the latter case
'deps' is not used so that the constraints defined in 'deps' are not
used. This could lead to failures on stable branches when new packages
are released that break the build. To avoid this, the simplest solution
is to pre-install requirements, i.e. add requirements.txt to 'docs' tox
target.

Change-Id: I1d80bfc5f9c3fecc8551ffc8592e39f76b671485
"}]
commit_message:
[CI] Install dependencies for docs target

When tox 'docs' target is called, first it installs the dependencies
(listed in 'deps') in 'installdeps' phase, then it installs murano
(with its requirements) in 'develop-inst' phase. In the latter case
'deps' is not used so that the constraints defined in 'deps' are not
used. This could lead to failures on stable branches when new packages
are released that break the build. To avoid this, the simplest solution
is to pre-install requirements, i.e. add requirements.txt to 'docs' tox
target.

Change-Id: I1d80bfc5f9c3fecc8551ffc8592e39f76b671485

commit_message:
Initial commit for application policy

Commit includes:
* New package type Aspect which will have extended MuranoPL
  reflection capabilities. At this stage methods inside this type
  of packages have the ability to modify properties of any object
* New classes io.murano.policy.Aspect and io.murano.policy.Notifier
* Every aspect instance can subscribe to notifications of
  different events. For now it is only object initialization event.
  To subscribe, it passes itself, name of handler method and name
  of method to check some condition against the processed object
  to notifier's subscribe() method
* Example policy package that inforces usage of some maximum
  instance flavor with test-runner based tests

So now it is possible:
* to write custom aspect code in the form of library package
* to define the aspect rules in json-format and place it to the file
  murano/common/aspects.py (until db tables and api are implemented)

commit_message:
Extended MuranoPL reflection and package load event

1. Methods inside Aspect packages provided with extended
   reflection capabilities:
     * changing type property default value
     * changing type property contract
     * changing method argument default value
     * changing method argument contract
2. Aspects are able to subscribe to package load event
3. DefaultSetter and ContractSetter example policies are added

Change-Id: I141b1f80b2b1e8aaf97d167734fefeeecdd72fed
Partially-implements: bp application-policies

commit_message:
Add RecordSet resource and zone list

This commit introduces a new io.murano.resources.RecordSet resource
type. When coupled with a commit to murano-dashboard, it allows
users to be able to select an available zone from a UI list and
have it passed to this RecordSet resource for provising a Designate
DNS record.

commit_message:
drop mock from lower-constraints

The mock third party library was needed for mock support in py2
runtimes. Since we now only support py36 and later, we don't need it
in lower-constraints.

These changes will help us to drop `mock` from openstack/requirements

Change-Id: I676add1724c6557e3b0108222a2c2babe022c98c

commit_message:
Add networks properties for OS::Nova::Server resource

Since nova api version 2.37,  `networks` entry is required for the server
creation[1]. Plus a heat change[2] in release Rocky removes old workaround.
Therefore instance creation through heat orchestraction template needs
`networks` property of OS::Nova::Server resource in template.

While murano core library not passing this property to heat template makes
it fail to work with Rocky release heat.

The patch passes in `Auto` value to networks object for Instance class.

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/nova/latest/reference/api-microversion-history.html#id34
[2] https://github.com/openstack/heat/commit/3c06347a93343850409a243b3c7e1f11eeb4db3f

Closes-Bug: #1817538

Change-Id: Idef60e2c13e1d4f3ea802504076110ea447d193d

commit_message:
Remove -u root as mysql is executed with root user

As openstack installation guides suggest to run mysql with root shell
user, mysql will not ask for password, so in
controller-install-*.rst "-u root -p" is useless.

Related-Bug: #1785025

commit_message:
[Test-Runner] Added a 'save' method to TestFixture

Added a 'save' method to TestFixture class, so test-runner-based tests
may serialize MuranoPL-objects into JSON representation. The same
method may optionally run an orphan-cleanup routine to execute
resource deallocation for the objects which are present in object
store but are not part of the object tree passed to the function.

Change-Id: I51c017eb2582e43929a9fa7f51bab4e06b83f4e5
Closes-bug: #1597747

commit_message:
Fix toggle action of packages

In package page, there are two bugs:
1. toggle active and toggle public button text won't change.
2. toast only shows "Toggled Public" or "Toggled Active" even you toggle packages to private or inactive.

Change-Id: I5e984a408f3099f715f51af0483732863967df1f

commit_message:
Modify instance naming schema

When creating a new instance, generate its name based on
tenant name, application name and a region, therefore not using
a complicated composite structure used in Murano (murano+hashed),
and just UI generated name is displayed.

Also, the new schema takes into account names of the already
created instances to avoid duplication. For now, the 'hostname'
field for applications are still readonly, that would be changed
as validation is implemented.

Co-Authored-By: Artem Tiumentcev <darland.maik@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Roman Bogorodskiy <rbogorodskiy@mirantis.com>
Change-Id: I7bd0758cf4b04a01531c788ebedc06a5c98fe523
Signed-off-by: Leonid Bogdanov <lbogdanov@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Do not specify SESSION_ENGINE in murano-dashboard

Base openstack_dashboard/settings.py already sets to 'cache' backend
and it works just fine. Setting session engine to 'db' causes unwanted
complications and gives us no additional benefits.

Change-Id: I595a85471f344ea8a2b05a4f4ff00b9bdca865b5

commit_message:
Missing openstackId key when instances are not deployed.

This fix going to avoid a error 500 when the Instance is on the
Following states:
Deploying , Ready for Deploy or Deploy Failed.

Also fix bug that Stack names are not displayed on overview tab.

Change-Id: I3b1312db9e3ba94024a1c7fa64614cddfb6c6488

commit_message:
Add project parameter to filters resource with admin role

Currently, an user admin can list all profiles, clusters,.. and I
can using name, limit, marker when list. But, when I have so many
clusters, profiles, ... I can't list them only in a project.

So, I hope this patch can resolve above problem.

Change-Id: I76bf03478938b2b42996898a9538aa40cf2643ac

Add support a user admin can do everything

A user with role admin can delete, update cluster, policy, ...
and attach, detach a policy to a cluster and see policy biding
in a cluster

commit_message:
Retire Murano project

Murano project is in inactive list since 2024.1 and
have an open critical bug.
- https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/emerging-technology-and-inactive-projects.html#current-inactive-projects

and there is no leader in 2024.2 cycle.
- https://etherpad.opendev.org/p/2024.2-leaderless

There is no response on last call for maintainers and retirement
notification:
- https://lists.openstack.org/archives/list/openstack-discuss@lists.openstack.org/thread/U2HITVJSZ4TKGTA7LEAODBIUZBCYGBZX/

Seeing project inactivities, open critical bug, and no maintainers
for this project, this commit propose to retire this project.

Change-Id: I6fc0070586b83c93398f3c2837e45974b23ba249

commit_message:
Retire Solum project

Solum project is in inactive list since 2024.1
- https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/emerging-technology-and-inactive-projects.html#current-inactive-projects

and there is no leader in 2024.2 cycle.
- https://etherpad.opendev.org/p/2024.2-leaderless

There is no response on last call for maintainers and retirement
notification:
- https://lists.openstack.org/archives/list/openstack-discuss@lists.openstack.org/thread/GD37ISH3TUBH5RQ2CCRZ5YIHE5LHX6G2/

Seeing project inactivities and no maintainers for this project,
this commit propose to retire this project.

commit_message:
Use OSCaaS to speed up devstack runs

OpenStackClient has a significant amount of startup overhead, which
adds a non-trivial amount of time to each devstack run because it makes
a lot of OSC calls. This change uses the OSC service from [0] to run
a persistent process that handles openstack calls. This removes most
of the startup overhead and in my local testing removes about three
minutes per devstack run.

Currently this is implemented as an opt-in feature. There are likely a
lot of edge cases in projects that use a devstack plugin so turning it
on universally is going to require boiling the ocean. I think getting
this in and enabled for some of the major projects should give us a lot
of the benefit without the enormous effort of making it 100% compatible
across all of OpenStack.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/nova/+/918689
Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/ironic/+/918690
Change-Id: I28e6159944746abe2d320369249b87f1c4b9e24e

commit_message:
Fix cinder deployment script

Recently we introduced test jobs that consume
charts from either local or public Helm repos.
All the deployment scripts must use variables
OSH_HELM_REPO or OSH_INFRA_HELM_REPO
which by default point to local directories
but these new jobs set them to use HTTP repos.

Change-Id: I2e17790385c2bdc0b79607c240a47639c61365c0

commit_message:
Add TLS proxy for novncproxy

This improvement enables TLS encryption for the novncproxy service, even
when enable_haproxy is False. This change is beneficial for operators
who run deployments using an external Load Balancer with enable_haproxy
set to False, but still require TLS encryption for the novncproxy
service.

Signed-off-by: Robert Breker
Signed-off-by: Oliver Schmitz

Change-Id: Ibb33aaf200f460c83ddeb9d0656ccaa6a655f142

Change-Id: Ib1326852a5abe95811fe2aa2b6d03e7d4ca57959

Ply-Patch: Add-TLS-proxy-for-novncproxy.patch
Change-Id: Idd295a4d4ea265e33a42e4c86830ca9d968fb2be

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2024-05-09 16:49:50.000000000', 'files': ['metalsmith/test/test_provisioner.py', 'metalsmith/_provisioner.py'], 'message': 'Error with clarity when a bad upgrade was encountered

Metalsmith is generally used as a frontend for baremetal
provisioning such that a user can ask for baremetal to be
deployed with a simplified command line. The challenge is
it artificially hydrates together data from several queries
to return a list of instances which have been deployed
or are managed using metalsmith. The challenge is if someone
didn't create an allocation record, or if someone used the
metalsmith modules to do so when the node was in a maintenance
state, for example if BMC communication was not working.

The underlying challenge is this results in a lack of an allocation
record from being created. This can be manually corrected, and instead
of providing a vague error, metalsmith now provides a detailed error
with the command to remedy the error state through manual creation of
the allocation record, which allows "metalsmith list" to work as
expected.

Change-Id: I033a9925fe798f329b7bb9a629da0cd0f1202683
'}]
commit_message:
Error with clarity when a bad upgrade was encountered

Metalsmith is generally used as a frontend for baremetal
provisioning such that a user can ask for baremetal to be
deployed with a simplified command line. The challenge is
it artificially hydrates together data from several queries
to return a list of instances which have been deployed
or are managed using metalsmith. The challenge is if someone
didn't create an allocation record, or if someone used the
metalsmith modules to do so when the node was in a maintenance
state, for example if BMC communication was not working.

The underlying challenge is this results in a lack of an allocation
record from being created. This can be manually corrected, and instead
of providing a vague error, metalsmith now provides a detailed error
with the command to remedy the error state through manual creation of
the allocation record, which allows "metalsmith list" to work as
expected.

Change-Id: I033a9925fe798f329b7bb9a629da0cd0f1202683

commit_message:
Allow domain users to manage credentials

Credentials are associated with users so there is no reason we prevent
domain users from accessing the resources. In some services like heat
domain admin is used to generate keystone credentials and loosing
the scope check is required to continue supporting such use case.

Closes-Bug: #2062045
Change-Id: I140b302d879ce1cc1f8d8de9e666cc74278a977f
(cherry picked from commit 5ead95ffcc597517feed53170e2d2f77cdd311a1)

commit_message:
Bundle the os-brick library in the Glance image

Glance uses the os-brick library to attach and detach Cinder volumes
in case the Cinder volume backend uses iSCSI/FC/NVMeoF as the underlying
storage protocol.

One such case is when using volume-backend images with Cinder volume
backends that support volume cloning.

Change-Id: I2ba690d78c560bee6e9e4e562c9dbe4f2ce09318

commit_message:
Add qos_prefetch_count to variables

When rabbit_stream_fanout is set to true, rabbit_qos_prefetch_count
should be set to a positive value.

This also fixes defenition of transient_quorum_queue as if
rabbit_stream_fanout is enabled - transient_quorum_queue should be also
enabled. [1]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/oslo.messaging/blob/master/oslo_messaging/_drivers/impl_rabbit.py#L726-L736

Change-Id: Ia10d3945717f07051680e72552e38f2e2d4ddf12

commit_message:
Improve terminology in project-config tree

There is no real reason we should be using some of the
terms we do, they're outdated, and we're behind other
open-source projects in this respect. Let's switch to
using more inclusive terms in all possible places.

Updated playbooks and related code accordingly.

Change-Id: Ia471193921660aa5f2152ab63eaf570bee3ebcd0
Depends-on: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/requirements/+/917786

commit_message:
Remove SQLAlchemy tips jobs

The most recent SQLAlchemy and Alembic versions are now in
upper-constraints. As a result, this job has served its purpose and can
be removed. For more information, see [1].

[1] https://lists.openstack.org/archives/list/openstack-discuss@lists.openstack.org/thread/RBHXHTO3GUOOXVSZXD4C2O3TKDOH2QSC/

Change-Id: I68f786d4125e00708c45fcb81fc1ff9cbe059f27
Signed-off-by: Stephen Finucane <stephenfin@redhat.com>
Depends-on: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/requirements/+/879743

commit_message:
Ensure app/filter factory options exist

All middleware filters and apps enabled in pipeline should have
the corresponding factory option (use = ... ) but the lines may not
exist in case the config file does not exist or is generated in advance
incompletely.

Change-Id: I714fe28547ea8308d7e82b66687ea0f24f816cda

This makes all the image upload commands in the devstack plugin use
--file instead of stdin redirection, and also uses an absolute path.
One of the commands was already doing it this way. By doing the upload

commit_message:
[devstack] Upload images with --file instead of stdin

This makes all the image upload commands in the devstack plugin use
--file instead of stdin redirection, and also uses an absolute path.
One of the commands was already doing it this way. By doing the upload
like this, it makes the devstack plugin usable with the OCaaS devstack
mode (for faster openstack client ops) since we can't pass the image
stream via stdin. Most people will be using --file for uploading
anyway, so this is probably more realistic anyway.

Change-Id: I8d97ed731133d02aed46a078c50769692ad7ba04

subject: Implement variables to address oslo.messaging improvements
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2024-05-10 15:59:30.000000000', 'files': ['defaults/main.yml', 'templates/aodh.conf.j2'], 'message': 'Implement variables to address oslo.messaging improvements

During last release cycle oslo.messaging has landed [1] series of extremely
useful changes that are designed to implement modern messaging
techniques for rabbitmq quorum queues.

Since these changes are breaking and require queues being re-created,
it makes total sense to align these with migration to quorum queues by default.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/q/topic:%22bug-2031497%22

Change-Id: I7229673bfff823467f7d756ef41713acdf49756f

commit_message:
Implement variables to address oslo.messaging improvements

During last release cycle oslo.messaging has landed [1] series of extremely
useful changes that are designed to implement modern messaging
techniques for rabbitmq quorum queues.

Since these changes are breaking and require queues being re-created,
it makes total sense to align these with migration to quorum queues by default.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/q/topic:%22bug-2031497%22

Change-Id: I7229673bfff823467f7d756ef41713acdf49756f

does.

commit_message:
openvswitch: Stop using intermediate scripts

This will fix exit codes - details in bug.

Basically openvswitch treats TERM as something fatal (exits
with 143) and the only solution for graceful exit is using
ovs-appctl and sending exit command, just like ovs-ctl utility
does.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/kolla/+/905189

Partial-Bug: #2048130
Change-Id: I523018cb98944de60d7b95404deb7cebd641f33a

commit_message:
Add variable to globally control notifications enablement

In order to be able to globally enable notification reporting for all services,
without an need to have ceilometer deployed or bunch of overrides for each
service, we add `oslomsg_notify_enabled` variable that aims to control
behaviour of enabled notifications.

Presence of ceilometer is still respected by default and being referenced.

Potential usecase are various billing panels that do rely on notifications
but do not require presence of Ceilometer.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/openstack-ansible-plugins/+/914144
Change-Id: I061653c3976458c0161915b7273f1ee2c575df13

commit_message:
Add variable to globally control notifications enablement

In order to be able to globally enable notification reporting for all services,
without an need to have ceilometer deployed or bunch of overrides for each
service, we add `oslomsg_notify_enabled` variable that aims to control
behaviour of enabled notifications.

Presence of ceilometer is still respected by default and being referenced.

Potential usecase are various billing panels that do rely on notifications
but do not require presence of Ceilometer.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/openstack-ansible-plugins/+/914144
Change-Id: I85480e8a176abea22a1cfe167056fc163d2e6992
